# Alexandrovka, Meleuzovsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Alexandrovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Alexandrovsky Selsoviet, Meleuzovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 520 as of 2010. There are 6 streets.
Geography
Alexandrovka is located 30&nbsp;km northeast of Meleuz (the district's administrative centre) by road. Kutlubulatovo is the nearest rural locality.
